Introduction

JiWoo is a South Korean singer and actress under MODHAUS.

On September 14, 2021, JiWoo was revealed to be competing on MBC's survival show "My Teenage Girl". She was eliminated in the eleventh episode.

In 2021, JiWoo made her acting debut in the Kok TV web-drama "I:LOVE:DM".

On June 1, 2022, JiWoo was introduced as the third member of the girl group tripleS under MODHAUS. She made her debut with the first ten members of the group on February 13, 2023, with the mini album "ASSEMBLE".

On May 19, 2023, she was revealed as a contestant on Mnet's survival show "Queendom Puzzle". She was eliminated in the last episode after ranking 13th.

As a member of tripleS, JiWoo was placed in the sub-units +(KR)ystal Eyes, ACID EYES, EVOLution, Aria, and Hatchi!.
